│ state being carried over between different vectorization attempts within the same basic    │
│ block. Specifically, the `BoUpSLP::Graph` data structure, which stores the dependency tree │
│ for vectorization candidates, is not cleared after a vectorization attempt is deemed       │
│ unprofitable and abandoned. When a subsequent vectorization attempt in the same block      │
│ reuses nodes from the previous attempt, it accesses stale `TreeEntry` objects with         │
│ incorrect user information, leading to an assertion failure during cost calculation.       │
│                                                                                            │
│ To fix this, I will clear the `BoUpSLP::Graph` at the beginning of the                     │
│ `BoUpSLP::buildTree` function. This ensures that every vectorization attempt starts with a │
│ clean slate, preventing state corruption and the resulting crash.                          │
│                                                                                            │
